# DiscordJS Node Basic Bot

A simple Discord bot built with [discord.js](https://discord.js.org/) v14("14.19.3") and Node.js.  
This bot demonstrates how to set up a basic slash command (`/ping`) and handle interactions.

---

## Features

- Slash command `/ping` that replies with the bot's current websocket ping.
- Uses Discord API v10 and modern discord.js practices.
- Easy to understand and extend.

---

## Prerequisites

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (latest stable version recommended)
- A Discord bot token from the [Discord Developer Portal](https://discord.com/developers/applications)

---

## Setup & Installation

```bash
# 1. Clone this repository

# 2. Install dependencies
npm install discord.js dotenv

# 3. Check the `.env` file and make the necessary changes

# 4. Change directory to where the bot is and run it:
cd discordjs-node-basic-bot
node MyBot.js

